#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn35.150"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.150:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.150:0.2"
msgid "15. Navapurāṇavagga "
msgstr "15. The Old and the New "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 150. Nibbānasappāyapaṭipadāsutta → catutthasappāyasuttaṃ (bj) | sappāya 4 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.150:0.3"
msgid "150. Nibbānasappāyapaṭipadāsutta "
msgstr "150. A Practice Conducive to Extinguishment "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn35.150:1.1"
msgid "“Nibbānasappāyaṃ vo, bhikkhave, paṭipadaṃ desessāmi. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, I will teach you a practice that’s conducive to extinguishment. "

msgctxt "sn35.150:1.2"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha … pe … "
msgstr "Listen … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.150:1.3"
msgid "katamā ca sā, bhikkhave, nibbānasappāyā paṭipadā? "
msgstr "And what is that practice that’s conducive to extinguishment? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.150:1.4"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn35.150:1.5"
msgid "cakkhu niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "Is the eye permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn35.150:2.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn35.150:3.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn35.150:4.1"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn35.150:5.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ: "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus: "

msgctxt "sn35.150:5.2"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti? "
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn35.150:6.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn35.150:7.1"
msgid "“Rūpā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti? "
msgstr "“Are sights … "

#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn35.150:8.1"
msgid "“Aniccā, bhante”. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn35.150:9.1"
msgid "“Cakkhuviññāṇaṃ … "
msgstr "eye consciousness … "

msgctxt "sn35.150:9.2"
msgid "cakkhusamphasso … pe … "
msgstr "eye contact … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.150:9.3"
msgid "yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "The pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact: is that permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn35.150:10.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "sn35.150:11.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "sn35.150:12.1"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "sn35.150:13.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ: "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus: "

msgctxt "sn35.150:13.2"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti? "
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "sn35.150:14.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.136, sc15
msgctxt "sn35.150:15.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati, rūpesupi nibbindati, cakkhuviññāṇepi nibbindati, cakkhusamphassepi nibbindati … pe … "
msgstr "Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, sights, eye consciousness, and eye contact. And they grow disillusioned with the painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.150:15.2"
msgid "yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tasmimpi nibbindati. "
msgstr "They grow disillusioned with the ear … nose … tongue … body … mind … painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact. "

msgctxt "sn35.150:15.3"
msgid "Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati … pe … "
msgstr "Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.150:15.4"
msgid "nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāti. "
msgstr "They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.150:15.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho sā, bhikkhave, nibbānasappāyā paṭipadā”ti. "
msgstr "This is that practice that’s conducive to extinguishment.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.150:15.6"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

